{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]On a hill far away stood an old rugged [C]cross
The [D7]emblem of suffering and [G]shame
And I love that old cross where the dearest and [C]best
For a [D7]world of lost sinners was [G]slain
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
So [D7]I’ll cherish the old rugged [G]cross
Till my [C]trophies at last I lay [G]down
I will cling to the old rugged [C]cross
And [G]exchange it someday [D7]for a [G]crown
{end_of_verse}

